@6003 = ~The Dancing Couple's Sword~
@6004 = ~Long Sword +2: Ras, The Dancing Couple's Sword
Beroalf was a barbarian who traveled from the cold north in search of adventure. He sought treasures and glory, but soon all he wanted were companions to share in the excitement of battle, much like those he had left behind in his faraway village. Unfortunately, his coarse remarks and rudimentary hygiene repelled most travelers he met, until he expressed his thoughts to a sympathetic mage. The mage, for a price, constructed Ras, the dancing blade. Though not quite what Beroalf had in mind, he was thrilled nonetheless, and wielded the sword for many years. How they were ultimately separated is not known.

This blade was found some years later by another group of adventurers and, while novel, it was not particularly useful. Not wanting to sell this item and let others benefit from its fresh scent, the party decided to keep it and show it to a smith. With the proper reagents, instead of the blade leaving the wielder's hand, a mirror image of it was cast and the weapon would remain. Splitting the sword decreased the accuracy of the original and the facscimile until the spell ran out, however. 

In the process of enhancing the sword, the smith also discovered the secret of the sword's fresh scent; some form of enchanted baking powder only produced by a wandering half-elf known as Armand Ha'mer for the (not so) rare occasions when he travelled with smelly companions. The powder had stored years and years of a barbarian's stink and that of others; as the craftsman found this out the hard way. With an eye towards using every characteristic do aid a client's adventuring, the craftsman knew instantly, after recovering his senses, such a powerful stink had it's uses. The united sword would now have the ability to cast 'stinking cloud' at an opponent once per day. 

STATISTICS:

